cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and specifically on salient object detection using RGB-D information. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new dataset and benchmark for evaluating salient object detection models, which involves machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, making cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. The proposed model also involves depth map filtering, which is related to robotics (RO) and multimedia (MM) applications, making these sub-categories also possible.
